  "course_description": "Students write and report for newspapers, radio, magazines, online sites and social media and develop websites to publish multimedia writing and news reports. They learn the basics of news writing and reporting, interviewing, and audio and video production. No journalism background required.",
  "course_notes": "This course invites students to engage with journalism across textual, audio, visual, hybrid, and interactive modes. Students will study local and global news, and pursue research based on topics of interest to build new, true, and medium-specific projects. The course will guide students through the journalistic process, from brainstorming topics to observing events, interviewing subjects, and pitching stories.",
